Excellent — DLQ is where operational maturity really shows. The key is to make DLQ entries actionable (why did it fail, can it be replayed, what blast radius), and to avoid noisy alert storms.

Below is a production-oriented pattern for BullMQ:

- Any terminal failure (retry exhausted OR `UnrecoverableError`) gets forwarded to `jobs:deadletter`.
- DLQ payload includes replay metadata, failure classification, attempt history, timestamps, and source queue context.
- Alert fan-out:
  - Critical queue terminal failures => Slack + PagerDuty (high urgency)
  - Standard/bulk => Slack (lower urgency, optional PD thresholds)
- Idempotent forwarding so one failed job generates one DLQ record.

---

## 1) DLQ schema design

Use a consistent schema so replay tooling is straightforward.

```ts
interface DLQMessage {
  schemaVersion: 1;
  source: {
    queue: string;
    jobName: string;
    originalJobId: string;
    correlationId?: string;
    tenantId?: string;
  };
  payload: any; // original job data
  failure: {
    failedAt: string;
    reason: string;
    errorName?: string;
    errorCode?: string;
    stack?: string;
    attemptsMade: number;
    maxAttempts: number;
    isRetryExhausted: boolean;
    isNonRetryable: boolean;
  };
  replay: {
    eligible: boolean;
    recommendedQueue: 'jobs:critical' | 'jobs:standard' | 'jobs:bulk';
    recommendedJobOptions: {
      attempts: number;
      backoffType?: string;
    };
  };
  diagnostics: {
    workerHostname?: string;
    serviceVersion?: string;
    env: string;
    firstSeenAt?: string;
  };
}
```

---

## 2) Create queues + events

```ts
import { Queue, QueueEvents } from 'bullmq';
import IORedis from 'ioredis';

const connection = new IORedis(process.env.REDIS_URL!, {
  maxRetriesPerRequest: null,
  enableReadyCheck: false,
});
const prefix = 'acme:prod:bull';

const qCritical = new Queue('jobs:critical', { connection, prefix });
const qStandard = new Queue('jobs:standard', { connection, prefix });
const qBulk = new Queue('jobs:bulk', { connection, prefix });
const qDLQ = new Queue('jobs:deadletter', { connection, prefix });

const evCritical = new QueueEvents('jobs:critical', { connection, prefix });
const evStandard = new QueueEvents('jobs:standard', { connection, prefix });
const evBulk = new QueueEvents('jobs:bulk', { connection, prefix });
```

---

## 3) Terminal failure detector + DLQ forwarder

We’ll listen for `failed`, fetch the job, and decide whether it’s terminal.

```ts
import crypto from 'crypto';

type SourceQueue = 'jobs:critical' | 'jobs:standard' | 'jobs:bulk';

function isNonRetryableError(failedReason?: string): boolean {
  // If you wrap with UnrecoverableError, message often includes that marker
  return Boolean(failedReason?.includes('UnrecoverableError') || failedReason?.includes('NON_RETRYABLE'));
}

async function forwardToDLQ(sourceQueue: SourceQueue, jobId: string, failedReason?: string) {
  const sourceQ = sourceQueue === 'jobs:critical' ? qCritical : sourceQueue === 'jobs:standard' ? qStandard : qBulk;
  const job = await sourceQ.getJob(jobId);
  if (!job) return;

  const attemptsMade = job.attemptsMade ?? 0;
  const maxAttempts = job.opts.attempts ?? 1;
  const retryExhausted = attemptsMade >= maxAttempts;
  const nonRetryable = isNonRetryableError(failedReason || job.failedReason);

  // Guard: only forward terminal failures
  if (!retryExhausted && !nonRetryable) return;

  const dlqId = `dlq:${sourceQueue}:${job.id}:${attemptsMade}`;

  const msg = {
    schemaVersion: 1,
    source: {
      queue: sourceQueue,
      jobName: job.name,
      originalJobId: String(job.id),
      correlationId: job.data?.requestId,
      tenantId: job.data?.tenantId,
    },
    payload: job.data,
    failure: {
      failedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      reason: failedReason || job.failedReason || 'unknown',
      errorName: nonRetryable ? 'UnrecoverableError' : 'RetryExhaustedError',
      attemptsMade,
      maxAttempts,
      isRetryExhausted: retryExhausted,
      isNonRetryable: nonRetryable,
      stack: job.stacktrace?.join('\n').slice(0, 16000),
    },
    replay: {
      eligible: true,
      recommendedQueue: sourceQueue,
      recommendedJobOptions: {
        attempts: 5,
        backoffType: 'customExponential',
      },
    },
    diagnostics: {
      env: process.env.NODE_ENV || 'unknown',
      serviceVersion: process.env.SERVICE_VERSION,
    },
  };

  await qDLQ.add('job.failed', msg, {
    jobId: dlqId, // dedupe-ish
    removeOnComplete: false,
    removeOnFail: false,
  });

  await sendAlertsIfNeeded(msg);
}
```

Attach handlers:

```ts
evCritical.on('failed', async ({ jobId, failedReason }) => {
  await forwardToDLQ('jobs:critical', jobId, failedReason);
});

evStandard.on('failed', async ({ jobId, failedReason }) => {
  await forwardToDLQ('jobs:standard', jobId, failedReason);
});

evBulk.on('failed', async ({ jobId, failedReason }) => {
  await forwardToDLQ('jobs:bulk', jobId, failedReason);
});
```

---

## 4) Alerting: Slack + PagerDuty

Implement alert adapter layer (don’t hardcode vendors in core flow).

```ts
import fetch from 'node-fetch';

async function sendSlack(text: string) {
  const webhook = process.env.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL!;
  await fetch(webhook, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({ text }),
  });
}

async function sendPagerDuty(summary: string, severity: 'critical' | 'error', dedupKey: string, details: any) {
  const routingKey = process.env.PD_ROUTING_KEY!;
  await fetch('https://events.pagerduty.com/v2/enqueue', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      routing_key: routingKey,
      event_action: 'trigger',
      dedup_key: dedupKey,
      payload: {
        summary,
        source: 'bullmq-worker',
        severity,
        custom_details: details,
      },
    }),
  });
}

async function sendAlertsIfNeeded(msg: any) {
  const q = msg.source.queue as SourceQueue;
  const base = `[DLQ] ${q} ${msg.source.jobName} jobId=${msg.source.originalJobId} attempts=${msg.failure.attemptsMade}/${msg.failure.maxAttempts} reason=${msg.failure.reason}`;

  // Always Slack
  await sendSlack(base);

  // PagerDuty only for critical queue
  if (q === 'jobs:critical') {
    const dedup = `bullmq:${q}:${msg.source.jobName}:${msg.failure.errorName}`;
    await sendPagerDuty(base, 'critical', dedup, {
      correlationId: msg.source.correlationId,
      tenantId: msg.source.tenantId,
      originalJobId: msg.source.originalJobId,
      reason: msg.failure.reason,
    });
  }
}
```

---

## 5) Replay design

Create a controlled replay endpoint/tool:

- Input: `dlqJobId`, optional override queue/options
- Validate payload schemaVersion
- Add new job with `replayOf: <originalJobId>` metadata
- Record replay audit entry

Avoid “replay all blindly”; always support filtering by error code/time window.

---

## 6) Noise controls

- Add rate-limiting/batching for Slack alerts (e.g., aggregate similar failures per 5 min).
- Use PagerDuty dedup keys to suppress incident floods.
- Alert only on terminal failures, not each failed attempt.

---

